bital angular\nmomentum. These excitonic energy levels are experimentally found robust against\nenvironmental perturbations. The discovery of excitonic dark states and\nexceptionally large binding energy not only sheds light on the importance of\nmany-electron effects in this two-dimensional gapped system, but also holds\nexciting potentials for the device application of TMDC monolayers and their\nheterostructures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Mar 2014 20:17:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-16"}
